  "text": "For a Boolean function of n inputs, there are 2 n+1 n! distinct NPN transformations. We denote a transformation by a vector of literals to indicate the permutation and phases of the inputs and a indicating the polarity of the output. For example, applying transformation τ = ( , , , ̅ ) to function ( , , ) = + results in a new function ∘ τ = + , which replaces with , and with respectively, while also negating the output. [CITATION_1] . There are a number of efficient algorithms in the literatures for symmetry detection [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
